  <h1>What is SAC Code?</h1>
  <div class="byline"><span class="av">SR</span><b>NumberIQ Glossary</b><span class="sep"></span><span>Last reviewed June 2026</span></div>
</header>
<div class="divide"></div>

<article class="prose read">
  <p class="answer-first lead"><b>A SAC (Services Accounting Code) is the classification code used to identify services for GST rate and reporting purposes.</b></p>
  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <p>Like HSN for goods, SAC codes drive the GST rate on services and the digit-reporting requirement in GSTR-1 follows the same turnover logic.</p>
  <div class="callout law"><b>Reference.</b> CGST Rules; Notification 78/2020-CT.</div>
  <div class="faq"><h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
    <details><summary>What is a SAC code?</summary><p>A code that classifies services under GST, analogous to the HSN code for goods.</p></details>
    <details><summary>How many SAC digits are needed?</summary><p>The same 4/6-digit logic as HSN, based on turnover.</p></details>
  </div>
  <div class="key-takeaways"><h2>Key takeaways</h2><ul><li>SAC classifies services for GST.</li><li>Drives the service GST rate.</li><li>Digit requirement follows turnover.</li></ul></div>
